A '''sewage treatment plant''' treats domestic and industrial sewage or [[wastewater]] using:

* Physical processes, including [[screening]] and [[sedimentation]],
* Biological processes, including [[activated sludge]], [[fixed film]] filters or [[slow sand filters]], and
* Chemical processes, including [[flocculation]].

